00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:33,900
 our own ability.

263
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:35,900
 Advent put us here and say, you know what?

264
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:38,860
 Yeah, there is a perfect world when Jesus comes back,

265
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:40,420
 but yeah, we're here right now.

266
00:13:40,420 --> 00:13:43,500
 Yes, Jesus has come already, has established his kingdom,

267
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:47,500
 but that kingdom is not fully realized on this planet yet.

268
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:50,020
 That's why this planet, this city,

269
00:13:50,020 --> 00:13:51,540
 is still filled with darkness,

270
00:13:51,540 --> 00:13:54,600
 is still filled with greed and evil

271
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,620
 and all these problems that we're seeing.

272
00:13:56,620 --> 00:13:59,100
 We are stuck in the middle.

273
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:01,980
 That's the real meaning of Advent.

274
00:14:01,980 --> 00:14:05,340
 Yes, we have gratitude to us, Jesus,

275
00:14:05,340 --> 00:14:07,080
 and say, yes, God, we thank you for coming

276
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:08,860
 to do what we have experienced,

277
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:10,340
 what this world has already experienced,

278
00:14:10,340 --> 00:14:14,500
 but God, that is not enough.

279
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:18,260
 When I look at those news, when I look at those stories,

280
00:14:18,260 --> 00:14:21,300
 when I see those families being broken,

281
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:23,140
 when I see those people struggling

282
00:14:23,140 --> 00:14:26,380
 when they lost their home,

283
00:14:26,380 --> 00:14:29,100
 I knew that simply wasn't enough.

284
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:31,580
 We're not there yet.

285
00:14:32,380 --> 00:14:34,620
 And so if there's one thing that should happen

286
00:14:34,620 --> 00:14:35,920
 in the season of Advent,

287
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:39,300
 that there should be a longing from the people of God,

288
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:41,980
 there should be a cry from the bottoms of our hearts

289
00:14:41,980 --> 00:14:45,580
 and say, God, Maranatha, Lord Jesus, come.

290
00:14:45,580 --> 00:14:46,580
 You need to come.

291
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:48,180
 We cannot fix this problem.

292
00:14:48,180 --> 00:14:49,620
 I cannot do that alone.

293
00:14:49,620 --> 00:14:50,860
 We cannot do that.

294
00:14:50,860 --> 00:14:54,500
 We cannot make things any better

295
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:55,620
 or maybe a little bit better,

296
00:14:55,620 --> 00:14:58,500
 but we cannot solve all the problems here.

297
00:14:58,500 --> 00:15:01,460
 If you don't come, if your spirit does not come,

298
00:15:01,460 --> 00:15:04,500
 if your presence is not with us,

299
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:06,860
 we don't have what it takes.

300
00:15:06,860 --> 00:15:08,420
 We don't know how to do that.

301
00:15:08,420 --> 00:15:11,260
 We tried and we failed.

302
00:15:11,260 --> 00:15:13,980
 Advent is the season.

303
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:17,580
 Yes, I know we wanna celebrate Christmas,

304
00:15:17,580 --> 00:15:21,180
 but Advent is the season that forces us

305
00:15:21,180 --> 00:15:23,860
 to look and remind ourselves,

306
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:28,420
 yes, there is a tension created by our faith

307
00:15:28,420 --> 00:15:31,760
 because I believe Jesus would come back.

308
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:34,500
 So whatever I'm seeing right now, that's not right.

309
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,100
 That doesn't sit well with my heart.

310
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:38,540
 I'm gonna continue to pray for that.

311
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:40,780
 I'm gonna continue to pray for this process

312
00:15:40,780 --> 00:15:43,780
 when God's kingdom is expanding on this planet.

313
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:45,180
 I wanna be a part of that.

314
00:15:45,180 --> 00:15:48,200
 Advent should move us to a place

315
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:50,020
 where we look at Jesus and say,

316
00:15:50,020 --> 00:15:53,740
 Jesus, you are gonna come back as a judge, as a king,

317
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:55,060
 and please do that.

318
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:58,300
 Please come back or please fill us with your presence

319
00:15:58,300 --> 00:15:59,860
 during this season here.

320
00:15:59,860 --> 00:16:05,060
 Advent begins in the dark.

321
00:16:05,060 --> 00:16:07,180
 We have to sit in the dark.

322
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:08,980
 We have to wrestle with it.

323
00:16:08,980 --> 00:16:11,020
 We're not just gonna look away from it.

324
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:14,460
 We're not just gonna pretend these problems do not exist.

325
00:16:14,460 --> 00:16:17,900
 We're in a Christian bubble and we're feeling quite okay.

326
00:16:17,900 --> 00:16:20,240
 We're not gonna do that.

327
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:24,160
 When this city suffer, we say we're suffering with them.

328
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:25,620
 We're gonna cry with them.

329
00:16:25,620 --> 00:16:26,980
 We're gonna be with them.

330
00:16:27,980 --> 00:16:30,440
 Advent begins in the dark.

331
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:34,660
 Means we need a reality check.

332
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:37,900
 We need to admit that the world is currently held captive

333
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:42,400
 by sin and darkness and death and powers and principalities

334
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:45,140
 that are behind the systemic evil

335
00:16:45,140 --> 00:16:47,420
 and the issues we see in our world.

336
00:16:47,420 --> 00:16:50,780
 We do not and cannot pretend things are fine.

337
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:54,100
 We should start naming the pain.

338
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:59,100
 We should be prayerfully start to look into the darkness

339
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:02,500
 and take an infantry.

340
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:04,580
 What is wrong right now?

341
00:17:04,580 --> 00:17:06,780
 We should start praying into those things.

342
00:17:06,780 --> 00:17:09,620
 We should look darkness into the eye and say,

343
00:17:09,620 --> 00:17:10,500
 you know what?

344
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:14,160
 We don't belong here.

345
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:17,140
 There's something better God has promised.

346
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:19,860
 And so we're gonna like pray and say,

347
00:17:19,860 --> 00:17:23,860
 come God, we want heaven come on earth.

348
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:26,020
 That's what Advent is about.

349
00:17:26,020 --> 00:17:27,900
 It's not just about these two coming,

350
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:30,980
 but it's also about the present coming right now.

351
00:17:30,980 --> 00:17:33,540
 God, we're praying by your Holy Spirit,

352
00:17:33,540 --> 00:17:37,220
 come into this place, bring healing, bring comfort,

353
00:17:37,220 --> 00:17:38,700
 you know, bring restoration.

354
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:41,800
 God, come, we know this is what you wanna do.

355
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:46,660
 But Advent always begins in the dark.

356
00:17:46,660 --> 00:17:50,020
 We need to identify the darkness we are,

357
00:17:50,020 --> 00:17:52,180
 the darkness around us.

358
00:17:52,180 --> 00:17:55,460
 We need to identify the same kind of darkness

359
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:57,800
 that's perhaps also inside of us.

360
00:17:57,800 --> 00:18:00,300
 When we talk about greed,

361
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:03,260
 I'm not sure if I really do any better

362
00:18:03,260 --> 00:18:06,580
 than whoever caused the fire.

363
00:18:06,580 --> 00:18:08,340
 There are times like I also wanna,

364
00:18:08,340 --> 00:18:09,540
 well, for my own benefit,

365
00:18:09,540 --> 00:18:13,020
 I also wanna just exploit others.

366
00:18:13,020 --> 00:18:16,300
 I also just wanna take advantage of other people.

367
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:18,100
 When the chance present itself,

368
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:19,740
 I know I'm equally sinful.

369
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:24,740
 I know I also contribute to that darkness I see around me.

370
00:18:24,740 --> 00:18:30,100
 I gotta sit here and face my own darkness.

371
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:32,300
 We're not immune to the evil

372
00:18:32,300 --> 00:18:35,100
 that has torn apart so many families

373
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:37,940
 and destroyed so many lives this week.

374
00:18:37,940 --> 00:18:41,420
 And being caught in this tension

375
00:18:41,420 --> 00:18:45,020
 between the evil in this world and the goodness of God,

376
00:18:45,020 --> 00:18:47,660
 you know, between how things are right now

377
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:49,500
 and how things should be,

378
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:53,940
 that would bring us a lot of questions.

379
00:18:53,940 --> 00:18:55,180
 Or it would bring us to a place

380
00:18:55,180 --> 00:18:56,620
 where we will be wrestling

381
00:18:56,620 --> 00:18:59,520
 with a lot of questions in our hearts.

382
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:03,300
 I'm sure a lot of people, you might have asked why.

383
00:19:03,300 --> 00:19:06,220
 I remember I was reading on threats,

384
00:19:06,220 --> 00:19:08,540
 if you know what's threats.

385
00:19:08,540 --> 00:19:10,100
 I was reading there, somebody would say,

386
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:13,660
 oh, I wish, you know, God would send rain.

387
00:19:13,660 --> 00:19:15,140
 And I'm like, me too.

388
00:19:15,140 --> 00:19:16,060
 And the next question is,

389
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:17,700
 how come God didn't send rain?

390
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:18,820
 How come this just happened

391
00:19:18,820 --> 00:19:21,120
 to be the driest week in the year?

392
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,500
 You know, God, you could have sent rain, right?

393
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:25,380
 You know, sometimes even during winters,

394
00:19:25,380 --> 00:19:28,300
 it just rain out of no reason, it just rain.

395
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:31,200
 How come the rain is not sent right now?

396
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:33,640
 How come, God, you could do this, but you didn't do that?

397
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:35,540
 How come this or that or that or that?

398
00:19:35,540 --> 00:19:37,420
 I have all these questions as well.

399
00:19:37,420 --> 00:19:39,040
 And when I read on social media,

400
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:41,580
 that's the questions that people ask

401
00:19:41,580 --> 00:19:44,940
 when they're suffering, when they're paying.

402
00:19:44,940 --> 00:19:47,860
 The common question is, where is God?

403
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:50,500
 If God is good, if God is powerful,

404
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:51,940
 why isn't he doing something?

405
00:19:51,940 --> 00:19:54,160
 Why does he allow all this suffering?

406
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:56,900
 If we're living in that tension,

407
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:59,940
 we're inevitably be brought to this place

408
00:19:59,940 --> 00:20:01,660
 to ask all these questions.

409
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:05,580
 And standing here as a pastor,

410
00:20:05,580 --> 00:20:08,580
 I just wanna give you my answer.

411
00:20:08,580 --> 00:20:09,540
 I don't know.

412
00:20:09,540 --> 00:20:11,940
 And I don't wanna pretend.

413
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:16,300
 I don't wanna just give some intellectual answers,

414
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:19,020
 which I know that would never satisfy

415
00:20:19,020 --> 00:20:23,020
 those broken hearts who are asking those questions.

416
00:20:23,020 --> 00:20:25,220
 We thought logical answers may solve the issue,

417
00:20:25,220 --> 00:20:27,900
 but no, they don't need a logical answer.

418
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:30,020
 They are just simply hurting.

419
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:35,020
 So church, if I could share this little tips,

420
00:20:35,020 --> 00:20:41,560
 this week is not the time for apologetics.

421
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:45,940
 This is not the week to explain the majesty of God,

422
00:20:45,940 --> 00:20:47,580
 the sovereignty of God to people.

423
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:51,260
 Wow, he's still sovereign, he's still mighty.

424
00:20:51,260 --> 00:20:54,700
 This is not the week to do, so we'll have time to do that.

425
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:57,420
 This is not the time, this is not the week.

426
00:20:57,420 --> 00:21:00,620
 If Jesus shows up right now,

427
00:21:00,620 --> 00:21:02,620
 he's not gonna give explanations.

428
00:21:02,620 --> 00:21:07,280
 He's simply, he's going to encounter people.

429
00:21:07,280 --> 00:21:10,900
 They need to experience the reality of Jesus,

430
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:13,580
 not just getting an intellectual answer right now.

431
00:21:13,580 --> 00:21:16,740
 I've been asking all these questions as well,

432
00:21:16,740 --> 00:21:19,260
 and I realize, besides the question of why,

433
00:21:19,260 --> 00:21:21,460
 one of the questions I ask sometimes,

434
00:21:21,460 --> 00:21:23,020
 and I've been reading Psalm lately,

435
00:21:23,020 --> 00:21:26,280
 and one of these phrase that comes up all the time

436
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:28,840
 in the book of Psalms is this phrase, how long?

437
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:32,000
 How long are you gonna ignore me, God?

438
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:35,440
 How long, my enemies are gonna triumph over me?

439
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:37,780
 How long, how long, how long?

440
00:21:37,780 --> 00:21:39,780
 When you see somebody asking how long,

441
00:21:39,780 --> 00:21:41,620
 you know they are in suffering.

442
00:21:41,620 --> 00:21:47,100
 Nobody wants Disneyland to end.

443
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:49,940
 Nobody wants a party to end.

444
00:21:49,940 --> 00:21:53,780
 When we're asking how long, it means we're suffering inside.

445
00:21:53,780 --> 00:22:01,180
 And perhaps, perhaps we need to carry a different answer

446
00:22:01,180 --> 00:22:03,640
 wherever we go.

447
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:06,900
 Perhaps when we face people who are asking questions

448
00:22:06,900 --> 00:22:11,900
 about God's goodness, or kindness, and power, and might,

449
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:16,100
 maybe we don't have to rush to defend God.

450
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:18,620
 You know, I've been a Christian my entire life.

451
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:20,460
 If there's one thing I learned,

452
00:22:20,460 --> 00:22:22,860
 it would be that God is my defender.

453
00:22:22,860 --> 00:22:24,580
 I'm not his.

454
00:22:24,580 --> 00:22:26,940
 He doesn't need me to be his defender.

455
00:22:26,940 --> 00:22:27,880
 He is mine.

456
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:36,440
 We have a hurting city, asking a lot of questions right now.

457
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:40,720
 Funny enough, they don't need answers.

458
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:43,120
 They don't need head answers from us.

459
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:46,240
 They need a real encounter

460
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:52,960
 with the God who left heaven for our sake.

461
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:57,140
 They need to encounter the God in the manger,

462
00:22:57,140 --> 00:22:59,240
 weak, humble,

463
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:04,440
 the God who chose to identify himself with the lowly,

464
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:08,640
 with a marginalized family.

465
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:12,160
 They need to encounter a God who could identify

466
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:14,640
 with their suffering,

467
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:17,680
 who willingly walk onto the cross

468
00:23:17,680 --> 00:23:19,360
 at the very end of his life,

469
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:22,280
 and say, "I'm willing to enter human suffering."

470
00:23:22,280 --> 00:23:26,380
 They need an encounter with this God,

471
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:29,440
 not just intellectual answers.

472
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:33,500
 And so, if you could, if we could,

473
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:35,520
 let's try that this week.

474
00:23:35,520 --> 00:23:38,640
 If you see someone who's hurting with a lot of questions,

475
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:42,120
 don't rush to give them answers.

476
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:42,960
 Give them a hug.

477
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:46,160
 Say a prayer.

478
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:47,220
 Just sit with them.

479
00:23:47,220 --> 00:23:50,860
 You know, Job, if you read the book of Job,

480
00:23:50,860 --> 00:23:53,800
 his friends are very eager to give him answers

481
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:55,560
 and very eager to defend God,

482
00:23:55,560 --> 00:23:57,640
 and you all see what happens.

483
00:23:57,640 --> 00:23:59,480
 So if you haven't read that, go back and read it,

484
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:01,900
 and you will see, you will know that's a very bad idea

485
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:06,140
 to give people advice and answers when they're in pain.

486
00:24:06,140 --> 00:24:08,940
 They need someone to say, "I know you're in pain.

487
00:24:08,940 --> 00:24:12,500
 "And because I love you when you're in pain,

488
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:13,920
 "I'm in pain as well.

489
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:18,300
 "I'm here to share your pain.

490
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:20,100
 "I'm here to share your suffering."

491
00:24:20,100 --> 00:24:27,180
 Advent begins in the dark,

492
00:24:27,180 --> 00:24:30,100
 when we're willing to sit in the dark with them,

493
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:33,460
 when we're willing to look that darkness in the eye.

494
00:24:33,460 --> 00:24:35,620
 But we don't stop there,

495
00:24:35,620 --> 00:24:38,420
 because, you know, if we have,

496
00:24:38,420 --> 00:24:40,780
 when we look at Advent this season,

497
00:24:40,780 --> 00:24:43,460
 it doesn't just invite us to sit in the dark,

498
00:24:43,460 --> 00:24:45,340
 but it also reminds us,

499
00:24:45,340 --> 00:24:48,500
 remind us that we cannot solve the problem ourselves,

500
00:24:48,500 --> 00:24:50,420
 just like what I said.

501
00:24:50,420 --> 00:24:52,140
 But there's someone who could.

502
00:24:52,140 --> 00:24:54,300
 Advent is the season that reminds us

503
00:24:54,300 --> 00:24:57,040
 who can solve those problems.

504
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:59,700
 We need a rescuer from the outside.

505
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:01,100
 We cannot fix our own worlds.

506
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:02,860
 We cannot rescue ourselves.

507
00:25:02,860 --> 00:25:06,820
 That's where the light comes in.

508
00:25:06,820 --> 00:25:09,340
 That's the central image of Advent.

509
00:25:09,340 --> 00:25:12,420
 When we talk about light in the Bible,

510
00:25:12,420 --> 00:25:14,660
 in times like this,

511
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:17,380
 we have to be very careful.

512
00:25:17,380 --> 00:25:21,060
 It's easy to talk about light.

513
00:25:21,060 --> 00:25:23,140
 It's easy to talk about this,

514
00:25:23,140 --> 00:25:24,980
 'cause we do that all the time,

515
00:25:24,980 --> 00:25:27,500
 and we mention light all the time,

516
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:32,500
 but if we light up every lamp in this room,

517
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:35,500
 and we just try to light a candle,

518
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:38,360
 and that candle will just be a decoration.

519
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:40,660
 Sometimes when we said, you know,

520
00:25:40,660 --> 00:25:42,300
 the light of Christmas,

521
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:44,100
 we light a candle in a bright room,

522
00:25:44,100 --> 00:25:46,780
 and still that light is just a decoration in our life.

523
00:25:46,780 --> 00:25:48,820
 Like, it's just okay, nice deco.

524
00:25:48,820 --> 00:25:51,180
 Oh, it's good for pictures.

525
00:25:51,180 --> 00:25:53,180
 Sometimes Jesus, we make Jesus just nice

526
00:25:53,180 --> 00:25:54,780
 for pictures in our lives.

527
00:25:54,780 --> 00:25:56,020
 Oh yeah, you know?

